---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const cmds = [
  ['/etmc menu', 'Open the etmc menu.'],
  ['/etmc host <network> [secret]', 'Host the current world on a network.'],
  ['/etmc join <code>', 'Join from an ETMC1: code.'],
  ['/etmc connect <url> [ip:port]', 'Fetch a config URL and connect to the server.'],
  ['/etmc status', 'Show role, virtual IP, peers and latency.'],
  ['/etmc invite', 'Copy the current join code to the clipboard.'],
  ['/etmc leave', 'Leave the network and tear down the instance.'],
  ['/etmc relay add|list|clear', 'Manage your relay nodes.'],
  ['/etmc hud', 'Toggle the status HUD.'],
];
---

<DocsLayout title="Commands" description="The /etmc client commands.">
  <p>All commands are client-side; they work the same as the GUI.</p>
  <div class="panel slot">
    {cmds.map(([c, d]) => (
      <p style="margin:6px 0"><code>{c}</code><br /><span class="muted">{d}</span></p>
    ))}
  </div>
  <p>The keybind <span class="kbd">G</span> opens the menu (rebindable under <em>Controls → Misc</em>).</p>
</DocsLayout>
